Suzuki has launched its new S-Presso in South Africa, with the compact SUV now one of the few cars that motorists can buy new for less than R160,000. The S-Presso shares its engine with the Suzuki Celerio, a three-cylinder engine which offers 50kW at 5,500 r/min and 90Nm of torque at 3,500 r/min. Suzuki said that this engine also has an average fuel consumption of less than 5 litres per 100km which also makes it a strong budget option. Below BusinessTech looked at five other cars which you can buy in South Africa right now for less than R160,000, and how they stack up. Mahindra KUV100 Nxt 1.2 – R142,999 Power maximum: 61kW
Torque maximum: 115Nm
